<span id="freeTextContainer5915656323468517494">This was a fun romp through Early Renaissance Europe with a Knight Errant. It was meant to be unrealistic, because no knight was as honest and true as Amadis, who miraculously recovered from many wounds, lost many horses, and saved many damsels. Funny how the song ‘Along Came Jones’ by Ray Stevens kept playing in my head. </span>

          </span>
